title: Navigating a neurotypical life I
post_data: Navigating a neurotypical life I imagine is hard and sometimes feels almost impossible. Navigating life and mental illness at the same time often feels *actually* impossible. A few months ago, I heard the term ‚Äúbipolar exhaustion‚Äù and I‚Äôd never felt more aptly described. When I say I am tired, I do not mean I need a good night sleep or an afternoon nap. title: Please read this. As you
post_data: Please read this. As you do, keep in mind that it‚Äôs often easy to center ourselves in places that aren‚Äôt ours to speak. If you make a mistake. Just apologize and do better. üíï Dear Cis People, When you realize you've misgendered someone, and you apologize, then you should STOP. FUCKING. TALKING. Do not follow up by telling me about your kid having taught you trans people exist. Do not follow up by explaining how you knew I was trans. Do not follow up by excusing your behavior. Apologize and then SHUT. THE FUCK. UP. This has been a PSA
